1. First of all, love the Lord God with your whole heart, your whole soul, and your whole strength.
2. Then, love your neighbor as yourself.
3. Do not murder.
4. Do not commit adultery.
5. Do not steal.
6. Do not covet.
7. Do not bear false witness.
8. Honor all people.
9. Do not do to another what you would not have done to yourself.
10. Do not become attached to pleasures.
11. Love fasting.
12. Relieve the poor.
13. Clothe the naked.
14. Visit the sick.
15. Bury the dead.
16. Be a help in times of trouble.
17. Console the sorrowing.
18. Be a stranger to the world's ways.
19. Do not give way to anger.
20. Do not nurse a grudge.
21. Do not entertain deceit in your heart.
22. Do not give a false peace.
23. Do not forsake charity.
24. Do not swear, for fear of perjuring yourself.
25. Utter only truth from heart and mouth.
26. Do not return evil for evil.
27. Do no wrong to anyone, and bear patiently wrongs done to yourself.
28. Be not proud.
29. Be not addicted to wine.
30. Be not a great eater.
31. Be not drowsy.
32. Be not lazy.
33. Be not a grumbler.
34. Be not a detractor.
35. Put your hope in God.
36. Attribute to God, and not to self, whatever good you see in yourself.
37. Recognize always that evil is your own doing, and to impute it to yourself.
38. Be in dread of hell.
39. Desire eternal life with all the passion of the spirit.
40. Keep death daily before your eyes.
41. Keep constant guard over the actions of your life.
42. Know for certain that God sees you everywhere.
43. Disclose wrongful thoughts to your spiritual mentor.
44. Guard your tongue against evil and depraved speech.
45. Do not love much talking.
46. Speak no useless words or words that move to laughter.
47. Do not love much or boisterous laughter.
48. Devote yourself frequently to prayer.
49. Fulfill not the desires of the flesh; hate your own will.
50. Obey in all things the commands of those whom God has placed in authority over you even though they (which God forbid) should act otherwise, mindful of the Lord's precept, "Do what they say, but not what they do."
51. Fulfill God's commandments daily in your deeds.
52. Love chastity.
53. Be not jealous, nor harbor envy.
54. Do not love quarreling.
55. Shun arrogance.
56. Respect your seniors.
57. Love your juniors.
58. Make peace with your adversary before the sun sets.
59. Never despair of God's mercy.
